main event: On September 7, 1958, at Ellsworth AFB, S.D., an object with intermittent red, green, and white flashing lights, and erratic rapid movements was observed for about 10-20 minutes. Radar contact was made with the object, which appeared to orbit in the sky. There were two objects, each about the size of a quarter, with two miles separation.
